fields.description:
Requested in [FSH-1001|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-1001], however other customers may be interested in the ability to view LOC added/modified/removed per a changeset. 

Currently we do not have lines modfied, but we do have lines added removed statistics which we can get via EyeQL. 

{code:sql}
select revisions group by changeset return revision, linesAdded, linesRemoved 
{code}

From https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-989

{quote}
For our setup, we have the webserver running on a different machine to cvs. 
As a general solution, I think it would be a nice feature to be able to access the files via ssh, or have fisheye somehow handle the rscyn for you. 
{quote}

Something along the lines of:

{noformat}
Hi Matt Quail,

Your new FishEye password is: PASSWORD

You may use this to log in at http://longneck:6060/foo/.
{noformat}
